Spicy Shredded Pork with noodles was excellent.  Three tasty dumplings were awesome. The beef noodle soup was great. Next time we are in Columbus we will be back!

Normally, I would avoid going to thr OSU campus area unless absolutely necessary. This place is so good that I would be willing to go eat there during an OSU home football game. Good prices, great food.  I especially enjoy the spicy beef noodle soup and the eggplant & shredded pork noodles.

Amazing food. I get the pork noodle every time and its always as good as the last. Its very filling and tastes very fresh. It has been closed for the last few weeks though. If anyone knows why or for long long, i'd love to find out.

Best Beef Noodle soup in town!!   I'm not sure about the other rice dish but according to people giving bad review always from Doordash.  Keep in mind that Chinese food suppost to eat while it's hot and fresh.  Not after sitting long time during delivery.

Ordered for the first time and was very disappointed... I got Mongolian beef and it came with mostly onions and just a few slivers of beef. I also ordered the Chongqing diced chicken with hot pepper and it was incredibly dry. Will never order here again.

Absolute hole in the wall place that's very easy to walk past. But you'd be making a mistake. There is nothing better on a cold wintry day than a bowl of beef noodles from here. Highly recommend the spicy beef bowl. Not a lot of room inside and it does get busy after classes start getting out in the afternoon and at lunchtime.
Always great!

Coming from a Chinese guy, this place is okay. Wouldn’t consider it to be 100% authentic, but it does scratches the itch when it comes to chinese noodles. Might try the asian dishes next time but the noodles are alright.

I've gotten take out from here a few times and it's a decent place. The menu is really hit or miss though. The General Tso's is solid but the beef with broccoli was terrible. They work best for take out since the place is so small and they really get your food quickly.

Cozy restaurant with amazing food. My friend and I split the braised beef noodle soup, spicy pork noodles and the egg and tomato dish. All 3 were amazing. They also had Chinese bottled drinks. I got the bubble tea and it tasted as good as if it had been made fresh in a store.

When you go to this fine establishment, you must get the noodle soup! Any of their noodle soups are incredible. My personal favorite is the braised pork noodle soup. It’s a little small, but you don’t notice when you’re enjoying your meal because it’s that good. Seriously!
